<HEADLINE>
<P>
TREASURE HUNT IN OLD WELL KILLS 4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TYRE, Lebanon 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four men who went down a well dating back to the Phoenician period in the hope 
of finding treasure suffocated and died, police said. 
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman said the four, who died last week, were among a group of 10 
amateurs who discovered the well in this southern port city, which was a major 
Phoenician trading center more than 3,000 years before Christ. 
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the well dated back to that period. 
</P>
<P>
The six other people emerged safely from the 18-foot-deep well, the spokesman 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
