<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHARING POWER -- Los Angeles School Board member Roberta Weintraub on Wednesday 
will host East Valley parents in a discussion of their role in the district's 
new councils in which parents and teachers share some decision-making powers 
with administrators. 
</P>
<P>
BIBLE READING -- A judge is to hear a request for a restraining order Friday 
that would bar the Salvation Army from conducting public Bible readings outside 
a business plaza. 
</P>
