<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN HIT BY CAR, KILLED ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 38-year-old man believed to be a transient was hit by a car and killed early 
Saturday while standing on an interstate freeway, the county coroner's office 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Daniel MacDonald was facing west in the left-hand lane of northbound Interstate 
5, about 900 feet south of Balboa Avenue, when he was hit at 4:45 a.m. by a car 
driven by Rick Maloney of Mountain View, Deputy Coroner Charles Kelly said. 
</P>
<P>
Maloney was apparently unable to avoid the accident and he was not ticketed in 
connection with the accident, Kelly said. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities believed MacDonald was a transient because he had only a 
Metropolitan Transit System card in his pockets, Kelly said. 
</P>
