in the half and also connected from 26 yards in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica (3-4, 2-4) was limited to 17 yards rushing in the first half. The 
Corsairs were only able to drive inside the Pierce 40 once in the first half, 
but Aaron McDaniel picked up a Charles McKenzie fumble at the Brahma 40 to 
squelch the only scoring threat. 
</P>
<P>
McKenzie ran in from two yards to open the second half and Charles Frazier 
added a one-yard plunge at the end of the third period to account for Santa 
Monica's scoring. KIRBY LEE 
