<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Dominguez Hills women's soccer team closed out its most 
successful season here Saturday with a 3-0 victory over San Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
The Lady Toros, ranked No. 2 in Division II, got first-half goals from Kristi 
White and Jenny Grasso and a second-half goal from White to improve to 18-2. 
</P>
<P>
Goalie Chris Pezzullo, who only had to record one save, was credited with her 
15th shutout, giving her a school career record. Freshman forward Heather 
Rolland had assists on all three goals. White, a senior, has 17 goals and 16 
assists this season. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State is 3-4. 
</P>
<P>
