<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. COVERT OPERATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am amazed and appalled by the U.S. government's claim of worldwide FBI 
jurisdiction. Knowing that there can be no legal basis for such claim in light 
of other nations' sovereignties, our government has refused to reveal the basis 
of its claim. Any self-respecting sovereign state can be expected to oppose 
what any civilized system of law defines as kidnaping within its borders. If 
there can be any doubt about this, imagine what the reaction of the Bush 
government would be were the Soviets to make such a claim for the KGB, their 
equivalent agency. 
</P>
<P>
Along similar lines, efforts to constitutionally repeal First Amendment rights, 
such as the move to amend the Constitution to provide for lese-majeste laws in 
the guise of protecting the honor of the flag, impugn and threaten our 
constitutional framework of liberty. Supporters of such proposals should be 
recognized as enemies of liberty. Those who have collaborated with such enemies 
by enacting obviously unconstitutional statutes of a similar nature have shown 
a profound contempt for our rights and have betrayed their oaths to uphold the 
Constitution. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN P. TESCHKE 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
