<P>
RANCHO SECO PLANT IS FINED $50,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Operators of the voter-closed Rancho Seco nuclear power plant in Sacramento 
were fined $50,000 by the Nuclear Regulatory Commission for failing to properly 
train key workers to respond to emergencies. The Sacramento Municipal Utility 
District, which is shutting down the publicly owned plant, said it would pay 
the fine even though the problems have been corrected. The NRC found that 43 of 
the 77 workers belonging to the core of Rancho Seco's emergency response team 
were not properly trained. 
