<P>
ANNIVERSARY 'SPIN' WORTH $1 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Pico Rivera landscaper won $1 million Saturday on the fourth anniversary show 
of the California Lottery's "Big Spin." Juan Reynoso, 58, who is married and 
has five children and 11 grandchildren, wants to use his winnings to buy a 
house and open a real estate business, said his son, Gilbert. Other winners 
included, Randall Sell of Stockton and James Mullins of Hollister, who each 
received $50,000. William Sager of San Gabriel, Gilda Jones of Los Angeles and 
Elizabeth Fucuals of San Jose each took home $40,000. Guadalupe Cavazos of 
Caruthers won $30,000. The $20,000 winners were Hugo Brescia of Inglewood, 
Robert Miller of McKinleyville, Terry Gartman of Newark and Segundo Llamas of 
Santa Maria. Fred Davis of Oxnard got $10,000. Over the last four years, 2,536 
finalists have won a total of $412.7 million in the game. Reynoso was the 199th 
spinner to win $1 million or more. 
