<HEADLINE>
<P>
PHONY MESSENGER ENTERS L.A. HOME; MAN FATALLY SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was shot to death in his West Los Angeles home early Saturday after his 
wife opened the door to an intruder pretending to be a Western Union messenger, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
David Elias Isaac, 47, was fatally shot by an unidentified man who forced his 
way into the home located on a quiet street in the up-scale community of 
Beverlywood. West Los Angeles Division police who are investigating the 
shooting said the gunman fled the scene. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the victim's wife opened the front door, shortly after midnight, 
after a man rang the doorbell identifying himself as a telegram company 
messenger. Since it was her birthday, she was not surprised that she might be 
receiving a telegram, police said. 
</P>
<P>
After she opened the door, a man forced the door open wider and held a gun to 
her head. Her husband, hearing a struggle at the front door, came to his wife's 
aid. During the struggle that ensued, Isaac was shot, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Neighbors said they heard at least five shots coming from the house in rapid 
fire succession. 
</P>
</TEXT>
