<LENGTH>
<P>
87 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
CHICO; 
</P>
<P>
TWO ADMIT DIGGING AT INDIAN BURIAL SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men have admitted digging at an Indian burial ground without a permit. 
Bruce Owens, 50, of Oak Run, Shasta County, and Frederick Lindauer, 55, of 
Manton, Tehama County, pleaded guilty to one felony count of unauthorized 
excavation of archeological resources on federal land. U.S. Forest Service 
rangers arrested the two men while they were digging with shovels in the Lassen 
National Forest about 30 miles north of Chico. The men had found arrowheads and 
small tools in a 1,000-year-old Yana Indian village site. 
</P>
</TEXT>
